In a teleconference interview during the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade, President Joe Biden and First Lady Dr. Jill Biden shared their Thanksgiving messages. President Biden emphasized the importance of coming together and giving thanks for living in the greatest nation. He expressed optimism and gratitude for firefighters, police officers, first responders, and troops stationed abroad. Dr. Jill Biden encouraged acts of kindness and reaching out to loved ones. They both emphasized the need for unity and treating each other with decency, despite political differences.